			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Calcium fluoride (CaF2) is an insoluble ionic compound composed of Ca 2+ and F − ions. It occurs naturally as the mineral 'Fluorite' (also called fluorspar) and as 'Blue-John'. This salt is the source of most of the world's fluorine. It is mostly found in the bones and teeth. It is a white crystalline solid that is commonly used in the production of glass and ceramics due to its high strength.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氟化钙（CaF2）是一种不溶于水的离子化合物，由 Ca 2+ 和 F - 离子组成。它以矿物 &quot;萤石&quot;（也叫萤石）和 &quot;蓝约翰 &quot;的形式自然存在。这种盐是世界上大部分氟的来源。它主要存在于骨骼和牙齿中。它是一种白色结晶固体，由于强度高，通常用于玻璃和陶瓷的生产。</common:generalComment>
